snippet.textDisplay: Prince Charles has talked about a slimmed down Monarchy for years once he becomes King. Perhaps the Sussexes knew they would eventually become redundant and wanted to be able to go out and still make money while they can, without so many Royal duties getting in the way? Hence, the financial independence reference. If this is accurate, Harry might has some resentment towards certain members of his family. Harry has looked miserable for the past year and Meghan’s unhappy appearance in the documentary of their African tour led to more questions than answers. The documentary made them seem like troubled people who are alienated from from his family and, fending for their own principles. There were the reports last Summer that Harry disappeared for days and nobody knew where he was. Harry’s fingernails in recent photos seem to be bitten to nubs, a sign of stress. I think there is something more going on here than their unhappiness about Meghan’s treatment in the press. Although, perhaps the Palace is pushing forward Meghan stories as a diversion from media focus on other RF members? The fact that they didn’t spend their son’s first Christmas with his family seems significant. Meghan even spent Christmas with his family while she was engaged to Harry! Then their was the Sussex’s tension fraught appearance on the balcony for the Queen’s Birthday. They seem like two people under a huge amount of stress at what should be a happy stage in their lives. The fact that they left Archie in Canada while they addressed this current issue in England seems like a protective move but why is that protection necessary? I think it’s too easy to blame Meghan for all of this. She is one person and she doesn’t have the power or infinite resources the RF does. It seems the Sussexes has been backed in a corner about something. Who knows what the problems actually are? What are your observations?
